<h1 id="constants">Constants</h1>
<p><code>const</code> is just like <em>let</em>, except you can't reassign it to a new value</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">function greet (user) {
  const name = user.name
  name = name.toUpperCase()
  //=&gt; TypeError: Assignment to constant variable.
}
</code></pre>
<p>Most guides now recommend using <em>let</em> and <em>const</em> instead of <code>var</code>.</p>
